            . I am in the employ of Evan Thomas, a <rs id="t18301028-56-viclabel312" type="occupation">linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301028-56-victim554 t18301028-56-viclabel312"></join>, of <placeName id="t18301028-56-crimeloc313">Ratcliff-highway</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18301028-56-crimeloc313" type="placeName" value="Ratcliff-highway"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18301028-56-crimeloc313" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301028-56-off310 t18301028-56-crimeloc313"></join>. On the 28th of July, at a quarter-past ten o'clock at night, the prisoner came and asked me to show him some purses - I showed him some, which he refused; while I was looking for some others he took nine silk handkerchiefs, and put them into his hat - when I turned round he was putting his hat on; he then threw the handkerchiefs down, and ran out - I pursued, and overtook him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301028-56-person556">
                  DAVID 
                  THOMPSON
               <interp inst="t18301028-56-person556" type="surname" value="THOMPSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301028-56-person556" type="given" value="DAVID"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301028-56-person556" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-officer. The prisoner was given into my charge - I saw him running without a hat, and four or five persons after him: I crossed, and saw Jones stop him - I had not lost sight of him; he had got about fifty yards from the shop.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, declaring his innocence. He received a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18301028-56-verdict314" type="verdictDescription">
